                            <comment id="14119372" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 05:30:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hm... If we check and we find that the application made a mistake and provided fewer args than the pattern requires, what should log4j do? I think we should probably throw an exception, and IndexOutOfBounds is a pretty good choice, I&apos;d say. What do you propose?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT - I agree with the comments below pointing out that not throwing an exception is better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119381" author="yogu13" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 05:36:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IMO logging should never fail ... we wouldnt like a process to quit because logging failed. Also the reason i raised the issue was log4j didnt behave consistently ..&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SimpleLogger implementation works quitely if i end up giving something like below&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;logger.error(&quot;Hello World {} in {} &quot; , null);&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14119396" author="yogu13" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 05:46:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also consider the case where the logging is done pretty much dynamic.. so one wouldnt be sure if the message generated to log has a placeholder within it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt;(...;...;...) {
 Sting s = &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// dynamically constructed string ... Here the user may or may not include the place holder
&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;[] param =  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// dynamically constructed param array
&lt;/span&gt; logger.info(s,arr);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixing the check for param array size &amp;gt; 0 should enable the user to use it such scenarios as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WDYT ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119399" author="garydgregory" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 05:48:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119402" author="yogu13" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 05:49:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;would a unit test be required ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119406" author="yogu13" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 05:51:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also notice org.apache.logging.log4j.TestLogger also has a similar code to that of SimpleLogger. Should that be fixed too ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119419" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 06:05:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assigned to Gary since he is working on this - I hope that is okay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree that not throwing an exception is better.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Gary, your fix covers the empty array case. Should we also cover cases where the user does &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;logger.error(&quot;Hello World {} in {} &quot; , new String[] {&quot;only one param&quot;});&lt;/tt&gt; - so the number of provided is less than required by the pattern?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT: on closer inspection this is not actually a problem; PatternMessage already handles this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119431" author="yogu13" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 06:15:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gary has beaten me in the race to fix this defect &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMO &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=remkop%40yahoo.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;remkop@yahoo.com&quot;&gt;remkop@yahoo.com&lt;/a&gt; we should let go the user on that one again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=garydgregory&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;garydgregory&quot;&gt;garydgregory&lt;/a&gt;  the SimpleLoggerTest.java uses the TestLogger Implementation which is similar to SimpleLogger for now. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How about setting the factory to SimpleLoggerContextFactory ?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; LogManager.setFactory(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; SimpleLoggerContextFactory) that should help point to the SimpleLogger
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119991" author="garydgregory" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 15:50:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopening for a commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119992" author="garydgregory" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 15:51:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Somehow my previous edit to SimpleLogger is gone. Oh well, I have better tests now anyway. See git master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14121389" author="yogu13" created="Thu, 4 Sep 2014 14:11:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;indeed! thank you Gary..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14121402" author="garydgregory" created="Thu, 4 Sep 2014 14:22:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you confirm that you tested (or not) the master code in your environment?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
